                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.94/644</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State (<persName type="from"
                            >Phillips</persName>) to the Ambassador in Japan (<persName type="to"
                            >Grew</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-10-31">October 31,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Grew</hi>: I acknowledge receipt of your
                    confidential letter of October 6 giving a review of factors in the
                    Russo-Japanese situation and an estimate of possibilities. We have found this
                    material very useful and are very glad to have your views. Your estimate and
                    ours are in accord. I am sure that you will continue to watch this situation
                    closely and we will of course count on you to inform us of any developments of
                    importance in connection therewith.</p>
                <p>Yours sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
